</div><br>
<p> Hot summer days, time to travel to the country, holidays, outdoor activities, and at the same time - the need for effective protection against mosquitoes, ticks, fleas and other blood-sucking insects that can ruin the hours of long-awaited rest, have come. Especially important is effective and careful protection for our pets, which are not suitable effective, but often unsafe aerosols and insect drops, which can be bought in the store. Many repellents contain substances that are recognized as neurotoxic. </p>
<p> Essential and vegetable oils can provide very effective, but at the same time safe protection from blood-sucking parasites. Their action is based on the fact that they repel insects with their smell, containing aromatic molecules that act as "enemy signals" on flying insects. </p>
<p style="color:#993300; text-transform:uppercase;">List of effective essential oils</p>
<p> Mosquitoes, mites, midges and bees simply do not tolerate the smell of essential oils of basil, clove, geranium, thyme, litzei, rosemary, tea tree, eucalyptus, citronella. </p>
<p> These essential oils perfectly protect the skin and housing from harmful blood-sucking insects. </p>
<p style="color:#993300; text-transform:uppercase;">This short list will help you choose the essential oil for the best protection against:</p>
<p> Ticks (best essential oils) - geranium or palmarosa </p>
<p> Ticks (also suitable) - hit, eucalyptus, lavender </p>
<p> Mosquitoes (most effective) - citronella </p>
<p> Mosquitoes (also very effective) - thyme, lavender, rosemary, Litzeya, carnation, geranium, eucalyptus, basil </p>
<p> Fleas - Orange </p>
<p> Black flies - sasafras, lavender, eucalyptus, cedar, citronella, peppermint </p>
<p> Yours - tea tree, rosemary, lavender, eucalyptus, geranium </p>
<p style = "color: #993300; text-transform: uppercase;"> List of vegetable oils against mosquitoes and insects </p>
<p> Indian oil it is considered the oldest insecticide, not only against mosquitoes, but also "small domestic animals" - ants, bedbugs, and other living creatures. It is also used in the garden for the natural protection of plants from aphids and blackflies. </p>
<p style = "color: #993300; text-transform: uppercase;"> List of essential oils that soothe itching after a bite </p>
<p> Essential oils of lavender and tea tree help with mosquito bites - they relieve swelling, itching, redness and remove the allergic reaction from the skin. </p>
<p> Do not forget that essential oils become effective and repel mosquitoes, they must be natural and high quality. </p>
<p style = "color: #993300; text-transform: uppercase;"> Effective blends of mosquito essential oils </p>
<p> - 5 drops of peppermint essential oil, 5 drops of lavender essential oil; </p>
<p> - 5 drops of lavender essential oil, 5 drops of peppermint essential oil, 5 drops of clove essential oil; </p>
<p> - 5 drops of tea tree essential oil, 5 drops of clove essential oil, 5 drops of lavender essential oil; </p>
<p> - 5 drops of cedar essential oil, 5 drops of lavender essential oil. </p>
<p> In all these mixtures, lavender essential oil is used, which is ideal for dogs and young children and makes these mixtures softer and safer. </p>
<p style = "color: #993300; text-transform: uppercase;"> Methods of using essential oils to protect against insects </p>
<p> Aroma lamp: drop 5-7 drops of essential oil into the aroma lamp bowl, add hot water and light a candle. </p>
<p> Aromatic mosquito spray: 10 drops of essential oil, 10 ml of alcohol and 100 ml of water - pour the mixture into a bottle-spray and spray the room from this spray bottle. </p>
<p> These sprays can also handle clothes before another outing into the woods or the pond. Scented candles: make scented candles on the basis of essential oils and light them in the evening in the garden and on the windowsill. You can take a ready-made candle, add a few drops of citronella essential oil and light it. </p>
<p> Mosquito Oil: Make mosquito oil to treat exposed skin based on selected essential oils, following our recipes below. </p>
<p> Wet the napkin: Soak a cloth napkin (towel) with a mixture of water and selected essential oils and place it by the bed before going to bed. At night you will sleep well. </p>
<p> Make a cosmetic: Mix selected mosquito essential oil with unscented body cream. Rub the open areas of the body with the obtained agent - mosquitoes will not even fly up to you! </p>
<p> Make a mosquito bracelet: a repellent insect repellent bracelet is a very popular remedy that contains natural citronella essential oil. You can make such a bracelet yourself by dripping a few drops of essential oil on wooden beads or a wide ribbon, and tie it around your wrist. </p>
<p style = "color: #993300; text-transform: uppercase;"> Recipe for mosquito oil </p>
<p> 2 tbsp. vegetable oil base (for example, almond oil, apricot, grape seed) 10 cap. essential oil from the list above (optional) or a mixture. Apply a few drops on clothing and / or skin. If you are pregnant, or you use the tool for young children, consult your doctor. Also, this tool is desirable to handle all wet and damp places - flower pots, roof gutters, porch, window frames. </p>
<p style = "color: #993300; text-transform: uppercase;"> Anti-tick remedy </p>
<p> - 2 tbsp. vegetable oil base (if you will make a means to kill ticks for dogs, then use sweet almond oil, it contains a small amount of sulfur, which also acts on ticks) </p>
<p> - 10-25 cap. essential oil of geranium or palmarosis </p>
<p> Mix the essential oil and base oil, the mixture is stored for 6 months. </p>
<p> To protect against ticks, apply a few drops of the mixture on clothing and skin, avoiding the area around the eyes. In addition to the geranium essential oil of geranium, for the protection against ticks, you can use em palmarosis, it is cheaper, but has the same properties. </p>
<p style = "color: #993300; text-transform: uppercase;"> Spray from ticks </p>
<p> A more convenient option for spraying, you can also spray your bedding and clothes, as well as places where pets sleep. </p>
<p> 1-2 tsp essential oil of geranium or palmarosis </p>
<p> 200 ml. water </p>
<p> a little emulsifier (alcohol, for example) </p>
<p> spray bottle </p>
<p style = "color: #993300; text-transform: uppercase;"> Removing a mosquito bite itch </p>
<p> To relieve itching, you can wipe the bites with essential oil of lavender or tea tree, diluted in base oil (almond, grape seed, apricot) in dosage: </p>
<p> 3 - 6 drops of essential oil of choice </p>
<p> 25 ml of almond or apricot kernel base oil </p>
<p style = "color: #993300; text-transform: uppercase;"> A mixture of essential oils from bites is also effective: </p>
<p> 2 drops of eucalyptus radiate essential oil and 2 drops of tea tree essential oil - mix these oils with 1 teaspoon of base oil. </p>
<p> With this mixture, wipe the mosquito bite, and it miraculously relieves itching and swelling. </p>
<p> It can also be used with a wasp sting. </p>
<p> We hope that these effective tools will help you spend the summer with joy and without annoying insects! </p>
